10911750@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Before being allowed to do some action on a [[website]], the user is presented with alphanumerical characters in a distorted graphic image and asked to recognise it.@1@27@@oe@30-11-2008
10911760@unknown@formal@none@1@S@This is intended to prevent automated systems from abusing the site.@1@11@@oe@30-11-2008
10911770@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The rationale is that software sufficiently sophisticated to read the distorted image accurately does not exist (or is not available to the average user), so any system able to do so is likely to be a human being.@1@38@@oe@30-11-2008
